If the pool is being filled at a rate of $g cubic feet per minute, how
fast is the water level rising when the depth of water is $h feet?
$PAR

We first need to express the volume of water in the pool as a function
of \(h\), the depth of water in the pool. We find that
$BR
\(V=\) \{ans_rule(30)\} if \(h\le\)\{ans_rule(5)\}
$BR
and that \(V=\) \{ans_rule(30)\} if \(h>\)\{ans_rule(5)\}
$BR
Thus at the time in question, the water level is rising at a rate of
\{ans_rule()\} feet per minute.
